description:
Create the two client-side hooks that power the review session logic. Both live in src/components/core/AtRiskReview/.

HOOK 1 — useAtRiskReview.ts
Responsibilities:
- Calls api.item.getAtRiskItems.useQuery() and filters the result client-side using getDaysUntilExpiration (src/utils/expiration.ts) to only include FRESH items with <= 3 days remaining.
- Maintains queue state: CombinedItemType[] (items not yet decided), results: ReviewResult[], and currentItem (head of queue).
- Exposes an advance(decision: ReviewDecision) function that records the decision, fires the appropriate tRPC mutation, and pops the queue.
- Uses api.item.updateItem.useMutation (existing mutation — no new API needed) to persist each decision immediately when advance() is called:
    - eaten  → { status: EATEN, percentConsumed: 100 }
    - discarded → { status: DISCARDED }
    - updated → { percentConsumed, status } from the inline detail panel
    - skipped → no mutation, just pops the queue
- On mutation success, invalidates api.item.getItems so the Inventory list stays in sync.
- Exposes isLoading (query pending), isEmpty (queue.length === 0), and summary counts (eatenCount, discardedCount, skippedCount) for the completion screen.

Types:
  type ReviewDecision =
    | { type: 'eaten' }
    | { type: 'discarded' }
    | { type: 'updated'; percentConsumed: number; status?: ItemStatusType }
    | { type: 'skipped' };

  interface ReviewResult {
    itemId: number;
    decision: ReviewDecision;
  }

HOOK 2 — useAtRiskReviewSession.ts
Responsibilities:
- localStorage key: 'broccoli:atRiskReview:lastCompletedDate'
- shouldShowReview(): boolean — returns true if localStorage is empty OR if the stored date is not today (comparison via .toDateString()).
- markComplete(): void — writes new Date().toISOString() to localStorage AND calls api.user.markReviewComplete.mutate() to persist cross-device.
- forceOpen state: boolean — can be set to true externally (by the push notification deep-link handler) to bypass the localStorage gate.
- Exposes: shouldShow (derived from shouldShowReview() + forceOpen), markComplete(), setForceOpen().

DEPENDS ON: tRPC procedures issue (broccoli-dashboard-k5p).

Update both service worker files to handle the AT_RISK_REVIEW notification type and open the review deck when the notification is tapped. There are two service worker files that need identical updates: public/sw-push.js and src/sw-custom.js.

CHANGES TO notificationclick handler in both files:

Current behavior: all notifications open /app.
New behavior: notifications with data.type === 'AT_RISK_REVIEW' open /app?intent=review. If the app window is already open, send a postMessage instead of navigating so the user is not disrupted.

UPDATED HANDLER:

  self.addEventListener('notificationclick', function(event) {
    console.log('[SW Push] Notification click received.');
    event.notification.close();

    const data = event.notification.data || {};
    let urlToOpen = '/app';

    if (data.type === 'AT_RISK_REVIEW') {
      urlToOpen = '/app?intent=review';
    }

    event.waitUntil(
      clients.matchAll({ type: 'window', includeUncontrolled: true })
        .then(function(clientList) {
          for (let i = 0; i < clientList.length; i++) {
            const client = clientList[i];
            if (client.url.includes('/app') && 'focus' in client) {
              // App is already open — send a message to trigger the deck without navigation
              if (data.type === 'AT_RISK_REVIEW') {
                client.postMessage({ type: 'OPEN_AT_RISK_REVIEW' });
              }
              return client.focus();
            }
          }
          // App not open — open new window with intent param
          if (clients.openWindow) {
            return clients.openWindow(urlToOpen);
          }
        })
    );
  });

WHY postMessage vs URL param:
- If the user already has the app open, a URL navigation would cause a page reload or at minimum disrupt their current scroll position. postMessage lets the AtRiskReviewModal listen for OPEN_AT_RISK_REVIEW and open the deck in-place.
- If the app is not open, the ?intent=review query param is the signal — AtRiskReviewModal reads it via nuqs on mount.

ALSO UPDATE sw-push.js showNotification call to pass the tag field for OS-level deduplication:

  notificationData = {
    ...
    tag: data.data?.type === 'AT_RISK_REVIEW' ? 'at-risk-review' : (data.data?.itemId ? 'item-' + data.data.itemId : 'notification'),
    ...
  };

This ensures if a second AT_RISK_REVIEW notification somehow fires the same day, the OS replaces the existing one in the notification tray rather than stacking a duplicate.

TESTING:
- Send a test push with data: { type: 'AT_RISK_REVIEW' } via /api/push/send
- Verify clicking it opens /app?intent=review when app is closed
- Verify clicking it sends postMessage when app is already open
- Verify the existing ITEM_EXPIRING flow is unaffected

